	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64248346"><p>"They fucked themselves over <i>again</i>..."</p><p>FTFY.  This is a repeating cycle among farmers, probably has been since the invention of the plow.  A few good years, borrow money/seed/equipment to expand, then comes a bad year or two and they lose the farm.  Even worse, farmers tend to follow fashions.  When they see a neighbor doing well at something they'll copy it along with everyone else until the market is flooded with product, then they lose the farm.  Wash, rinse, repeat.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64248346">

